V1tfTN6guHQ==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dependencies for Jackson**\\n\\nI’m considering if I could add dependencies. The user mentioned they already added the generator, but I might need to provide Jackson annotations. I wonder if importing JacksonModule works, but maybe I need to check the compile import for annotations. \\n\\nIt seems the module’s Maven setup might not provide all dependencies, and perhaps adding explicit testImplementation for jackson-annotations could help. It looks like I need to edit build.gradle to align versions without hardcoding. There’s a lot to think through here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing dependency versions**\\n\\nI’m trying to figure out if it’s acceptable to hardcode the version for different artifacts in normal test inputs and assertions. While build dependencies often allow for hardcoded versions, it’s tricky if the module is missing transitive dependencies. I wonder if using `testImplementation \\\"com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-annotations:2.18.2\\\"` is a good idea. \\n\\nI need to inspect the POM, but it seems to be unavailable online. It's essential to ensure my tests are properly structured, especially with nested enums containing `$`. Also, I should confirm the schema version and look into JSON assertions for clarity.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Generating enums in JSON**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to generate enums directly, which should look like this: `{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"enum\\\":[\\\"...\\\"]}` using SchemaVersion.DRAFT_7. I need to use both ObjectNode and JsonNode for this. I want to ensure I handle the method invocation with @JsonValue without any arguments on the enum. I should also getDeclaredField via @JsonProperty for all constants and consider using the FLATTENED_ENUMS_FROM_JSONPROPERTY option. It might be best to create separate tests to verify the JSON value path with the first call.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_g1e6Lwt4gioxQQxTpoQC7r5i|fc_0d1e644265c1d49e016a3f1e1c005c81948b2182d489125fe3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.github.victools/jsonschema-module-jackson/4.38.0/src/test/java/com_github_victools/jsonschema_module_jackson/CustomEnumDefinitionProviderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_github_victools.jsonschema_module_jackson;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonValue;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode;\nimport com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.OptionPreset;\nimport com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGenerator;\nimport com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfig;\nimport com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder;\nimport com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaVersion;\nimport com.github.victools.jsonschema.module.jackson.JacksonModule;\nimport com.github.victools.jsonschema.module.jackson.JacksonOption;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class CustomEnumDefinitionProviderTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void jsonValueAnnotatedEnumMethodDefinesStringEnumValues() {\n        JsonNode schema = generateSchema(JsonValueStatus.class, JacksonOption.FLATTENED_ENUMS_FROM_JSONVALUE);\n\n        assertThat(schema.get(\"type\").asText()).isEqualTo(\"string\");\n        assertThat(enumValues(schema)).containsExactly(\"draft\", \"published\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void jsonPropertyAnnotatedEnumConstantsDefineStringEnumValues() {\n        JsonNode schema = generateSchema(JsonPropertyStatus.class, JacksonOption.FLATTENED_ENUMS_FROM_JSONPROPERTY);\n\n        assertThat(schema.get(\"type\").asText()).isEqualTo(\"string\");\n        assertThat(enumValues(schema)).containsExactly(\"awaiting-review\", \"accepted\");\n    }\n\n    private static JsonNode generateSchema(Class<?> schemaType, JacksonOption option) {\n        SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2020_12, OptionPreset.PLAIN_JSON);\n        configBuilder.with(new JacksonModule(option));\n        SchemaGeneratorConfig config = configBuilder.build();\n        SchemaGenerator generator = new SchemaGenerator(config);\n        return generator.generateSchema(schemaType);\n    }\n\n    private static List<String> enumValues(JsonNode schema) {\n        JsonNode enumNode = schema.get(\"enum\");\n        assertThat(enumNode).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(enumNode.isArray()).isTrue();\n        List<String> values = new ArrayList<>();\n        enumNode.forEach(value -> values.add(value.asText()));\n        return values;\n    }\n\n    private enum JsonValueStatus {\n        DRAFT(\"draft\"),\n        PUBLISHED(\"published\");\n\n        private final String serializedValue;\n\n        JsonValueStatus(String serializedValue) {\n            this.serializedValue = serializedValue;\n        }\n\n        @JsonValue\n        public String getSerializedValue() {\n            return this.serializedValue;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private enum JsonPropertyStatus {\n        @JsonProperty(\"awaiting-review\")\n        WAITING,\n\n        @JsonProperty(\"accepted\")\n        ACCEPTED\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 796, "output": 2034, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25870, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782521348637, "responseId": "resp_0d1e644265c1d49e016a3f1e0524e08194b3f88776bdc32867"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_g1e6Lwt4gioxQ